==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seek
<hw>Seek</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sick.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Seek
<hw>Seek</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sought</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Seeking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>seken</ets>, AS.
<ets>s⟦emac⟧can</ets>, <ets>s⟦emac⟧cean</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧kian</ets>, LG. <ets>s⟦oum⟧ken</ets>, D. <ets>zoeken</ets>,
OHG. <ets>suohhan</ets>, G. <ets>suchen</ets>, Icel. <ets>saekja</ets>,
Sw. <ets>s⟦oum⟧ka</ets>, Dan. <ets>s⟦oum⟧ge</ets>, Goth.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧kjan</ets>, and E. <ets>sake</ets>. Cf. <er>Beseech</er>,
<er>Ransack</er>, <er>Sagacious</er>, <er>Sake</er>,
<er>Soc</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To go in search of; to look for;
to search for; to try to find.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The man saked him, saying, What <qex>seekest</qex> thou? And he
said, I <qex>seek</qex> my brethren.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xxxvii. 15,
16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inquire for; to ask for; to solicit; to
beseech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Others, tempting him, <qex>sought</qex> of him a sign.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xi. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To try to acquire or gain; to strive after; to aim
at; <as>as, to <ex>seek</ex> wealth or fame; to <ex>seek</ex> one's
life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To try to reach or come to; to go to; to resort
to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Seek</qex> not Bethel, nor enter into Gilgal.</q>
<rj><qau>Amos v. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Since great Ulysses <qex>sought</qex> the Phrygian plains.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Seek
<hw>Seek</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make search or
inquiry; to endeavor to make discovery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Seek</qex> ye out of the book of the Lord, and read.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. xxxiv. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To seek</b></col>, <cd>needing to seek or search; hence,
unprepared.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Unpracticed, unprepared, and still <xex>to
seek</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> -- <col><b>To
seek after</b></col>, <cd>to make pursuit of; to attempt to find or
take.</cd> -- <col><b>To seek for</b></col>, <cd>to endeavor to
find.</cd> -- <col><b>To seek to</b></col>, <cd>to apply to; to resort
to; to court.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧All the earth <xex>sought
to</xex> Solomon, to hear his wisdom.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>1 Kings x. 24.</au> --
<col><b>To seek upon</b></col>, <cd>to make strict inquiry after; to
follow up; to persecute.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>To seek</qex>⟦br⟧
<qex>Upon</qex> a man and do his soul unrest.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seeker</ent>⟦br⟧
